nge-my-hair#Index" target="_self"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-75_">Why Does Pregnancy Hair Change?&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></span></a></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-dc7d4f62--pregnancy-hair_500x.jpg?v=1628676749" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-dc7d4f62--pregnancy-hair.jpg?v=1628676749 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-dc7d4f62--pregnancy-hair_500x.jpg?v=1628676749 320w" width="835" height="535" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Pregnancy Hair Change" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-GEbAx hdezgK pf-76_"/><p class="sc-xiLah fvOkQT pf-77_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-79_">First, what on earth is causing all these pesky changes? You probably know the answer. Hormonal surges throughout pregnancy are at an absolute high, with oestrogen being the main culprit. This can cause all manner of things, from rapidly growing locks to dry limp hair – it can be hard to predict what’s going to happen next. Every mum-to-be is as unique as her hair! Now you know the cause, let’s have a look at what are the most common pregnancy hair changes, and arm you with our best hair care tips during pregnancy. Just because you’re pregnant, your hair doesn’t have to suffer!&nbsp; 

